RBC Capital Markets Hires Duval-Kieffer as Strategist in London

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-03-07T06:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/rbc-capital-markets-hires-duval-kieffer-as-strategist-in-london.html
  RBC Capital Markets  hired Christophe Duval-Kieffer as a global inflation-linked strategist based in
London to expand the firm’s fixed-income research coverage.  Duval-Kieffer previously worked at Standard Chartered Bank
Plc as head of quantitative strategies and developed markets
rates research since 2008, the Toronto-based lender said in a
statement. He has 15 years experience at firms including  Credit
Suisse Group AG (CSGN) ,  Morgan Stanley (MS)  and Credit Agricole Indosuez.  RBC Capital Markets is the investment-banking business of  Royal Bank of Canada (RY) , the country’s largest lender by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Doug Alexander in Toronto at 
